  "prompt": "What are the biggest misconceptions about Obamacare?",
  "response": "Some common misconceptions about the Affordable Care Act (Obamacare) include:\n\n1. It's a government-run healthcare system\n- Actually, it's a regulated private insurance marketplace\n\n2. It eliminates all healthcare costs\n- It provides coverage options and subsidies, but doesn't make healthcare completely free\n\n3. It forces everyone to use government insurance\n- It requires insurance coverage but allows multiple private insurance options\n\n4. It only helps poor people\n- It provides benefits and protections for people across income levels\n\n5. It's completely mandatory\n- There are exemptions and penalties have been reduced to $0 at the federal level\n\n6. It dramatically increased healthcare costs for everyone\n- Cost increases varied, with many receiving subsidized or lower-cost plans\n\n7. It covers undocumented immigrants\n- It does not provide coverage for undocumented individuals\n\nThese perspectives aim to provide balanced information about the law's actual provisions and impacts.",
